# Two-level functions + managers

## Layers

| Layer | Path | Imports |
|-------|------|---------|
| Level 1 | `**/functions/**/*.ts` | `import type` from `app/types/**` only. No NPM, no `i18n`, no other project files. Dependencies are function arguments (dependency injection). |
| Level 2 | `**/*_manager.ts`, `src/stores/S_*.ts`, `**/_data/**/*.ts`, IPC registrars | Full wiring: NPM, `src/`, `i18n` locale modules, level-1 `functions/`. |
| Vue SFC | `src/components/**`, `src/layouts/**`, `src/pages/**`, `App.vue` | When `scripts/*_manager.ts` exists: only that manager, child `*.vue`, and `import type` from `app/types/**`. Template + styles stay in the SFC. |

## Manager file naming

Level-2 entry modules use the suffix **`_manager.ts`** (underscore before `manager`), not `.manager.ts`. Examples: `dialogAppSettings_manager.ts`, `faKeybindsChordUiFormatting_manager.ts`, `someComponent_manager.ts`. Grep for `*_manager.ts` to list managers.

## No re-export shim files

Do **not** add a separate module whose only job is `export { … } from './someOther_manager'` (or the old pattern `faFooStore.ts` re-exporting `foo_manager.ts`). Import from the **real** `*_manager.ts` or `functions/*.ts` module that defines the symbol. The same rule applies inside a manager: avoid `export { helper } from './other_manager'` when callers can import `other_manager` (or `functions/…`) directly. Domain **barrel** files such as `keybinds_manager.ts` that `export *` from several sibling managers in one folder are allowed as a single discoverable entry point—not legacy alias files that duplicate one manager under an old name.

## Managers are wiring-only (`fa-two-level/manager-wiring-only`)

A `*_manager.ts` file must **not** define functions (`export function`, inner `function`, top-level `const`/`let` with function expressions, or **`class`** declarations). It only **imports** dependencies, **invokes** factories from `functions/` (or sibling wiring modules when level-1 cannot import shared deps), and **exports `const` bindings** to the returned API (for example `export const getFaUserSettings = storeApi.get`).

**Allowed in managers:** `export const x = create…({ … })` and `const api = create…({ … })` when the initializer is a **call** to a factory (not an arrow/function at the top level). **Arrow functions and small lambdas inside the factory argument object** (for example `getInnerHeight: () => window.innerHeight` passed into `createUseFeature`) are allowed because they are nested property values, not top-level manager bodies.

**Not managers:** Stateful **classes**, long-lived session objects, and multi-step wiring that builds `sessionDeps` from `window` / Electron APIs belong in **sibling modules without the `_manager` suffix** (for example `faFloatingWindowTitleDragPointerSession.ts`, `faFloatingWindowResizePointerSessionWiring.ts`) or under `functions/` when the body is pure and fully injected. Do **not** name an implementation-only module `*_manager.ts` just because it is imported from a manager.

**Renderer wiring siblings:** When level-1 `functions/` cannot import `window`, Pinia, or other project modules, use a colocated `*Wiring.ts` (or `*Session.ts` / `*Bound.ts`) next to the manager, same as Electron `*Surface.ts` / `*Api.ts` next to `*_manager.ts`.

Composable managers use the same rule: `export const useFeature = createUseFeature({ ref, computed, i18n, … })` with `createUseFeature` defined under `functions/`.

## Layout per feature

```
<Feature>/
  Feature.vue
  scripts/
    <feature>_manager.ts
    functions/
      <concern>.ts
```

Shared domains: `src/scripts/<domain>/functions/` + `<domain>/*_manager.ts` (and optional `<domain>_manager.ts` barrel). Electron: `src-electron/mainScripts/<area>/functions/` + `*_manager.ts` wiring modules.

## ESLint rule ids (CI)

| Rule | Role |
|------|------|
| `import/no-restricted-paths` (zones) | `functions/` import boundaries; who may import `functions/` |
| `@typescript-eslint/no-restricted-imports` | NPM denylist on `functions/**` |
| `@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports` | On `functions/**` |
| `fa-two-level/functions-only-type-imports` | AST fallback for level 1 |
| `fa-two-level/feature-scripts-layout` | If `scripts/functions/` exists, only `*_manager.ts` siblings |
| `fa-two-level/require-manager-when-functions` | Requires `*_manager.ts` when `functions/` exists |
| `fa-two-level/vue-script-import-allowlist` | Thin Vue script when manager exists |
| `fa-two-level/no-functions-import-manager` | Level 1 must not import managers/stores |
| `fa-two-level/stores-functions-layout` | Who may import `src/stores/functions/` |
| `fa-two-level/manager-wiring-only` | `*_manager.ts` has no local functions, top-level arrow/function `const`/`let`, or `class` bodies |

Plugin: [eslint-rules/faTwoLevelPlugin.mjs](../../eslint-rules/faTwoLevelPlugin.mjs). Run `yarn lint:eslint` after each migration.

## Exclusions

No two-level rules on: `**/*playwright*`, `helpers/playwrightHelpers_*`, `e2e-tests/`, `i18n/**/*.ts` locale trees, `types/**`, configs, `*.vitest.test.ts`, `*.stories.ts`.

